      • execute

        public void execute(java.lang.String inEntityName,
                    java.io.Serializable[] inPrimaryKeys)
        Description copied from class: AbstractBaseCommand
        This is the method executed in the IEntityCommand pattern. This implementation puts the entity name and primary keys into the attributes map of the command and then calls execute(Map inAttributes) inherited from IBaseCommand.

        This method catches and logs any exceptions that occur during the command executing.

        Specified by:
        execute in interface IEntityCommand
        Overrides:
        execute in class AbstractBaseCommand
        Parameters:
        inEntityName - the entity for which to execute the command.
        inPrimaryKeys - only the first entry processed Extract node name from keys and launch appropriate node
